revision.text:
{{Unreferenced|date=29 July 2015 (Wednesday) 09:42 (UTC)}} [[File:Soukei otsuka kofun.jpg|thumb|Sōkei Ōtsuka Kofun]] {{ウィキ座標2段度分秒|35|25|48.7|N|136|40|1.5|E|region:JP-21|display=title}} '''Sōkei Ōtsuka Kofun''' (宗慶大塚古墳) is a {{ill|zenpō-kōen-fun|en|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|12=draft|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Motosu|ja|本巣市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Gifu Prefecture|ja|岐阜県|12=draft|12=draft}}. It is designated as a {{ill|Prefectural Historic Site|ja|岐阜県指定史跡|12=draft|12=draft}} in Gifu Prefecture.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.pref.gifu.lg.jp/kyoiku-bunka-sports/bunka-geijutsu/bunkazai-zuroku/bunkazai-zuroku/shiseki/motosusi/soukei.html |title=Sōkei Ōtsuka Kofun |publisher=Gifu Prefecture |accessdate=2012-08-04}}</ref>
It is also referred to as Sōkei Kofun or Ōtsuka Kofun.
== Overview == * The tomb dates to the early {{ill|Kofun period|ja|古墳時代|12=draft|12=draft}} (late 4th century to early 5th century). The identity of the buried individual is unknown. One theory suggests it is the tomb of {{ill|Kami Ōne|ja|神大根王|1=Kami Ōne|12=draft|12=draft}}, a {{ill|Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|国造|12=draft|12=draft}} (Mino and Motosu Provinces), the son of {{ill|Hikozakari|ja|彦坐王|12=draft|12=draft}} and grandson of {{ill|Emperor Kaika|ja|開化天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}. * The front section of the tomb has significantly collapsed and does not retain its original shape. The rear circular section has also eroded and lost height. * The surrounding area has been developed as Ōtsuka Kofun Park.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://teikoku-eng.co.jp/jisseki/1504_soukei/soukei.html|title=Motosu City Sōkei Ōtsuka Kofun Park Opened April 11 |publisher=Teikoku |accessdate=2015-07-29|language=Japanese}}</ref> The remnants of the surrounding moat have been restored as walking paths.
* **Kofun Type**: {{ill|Zenpō-kōen-fun|en|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|12=draft|12=draft}} * **Dimensions** (current state): ** Total Length: 82 m ** Rear Circular Section Diameter: 42.3 m ** Rear Circular Section Height: 4.2 m ** Front Section Length: 31 m
== Location == * Address: Kawarada 390, Sōkei, Motosu City, Gifu Prefecture, Japan
== Transportation Access == === By Train === ; {{ill|Tarumi Railway|ja|樽見鉄道|12=draft|12=draft}} * Approximately 4 km from {{ill|Kitagata-Makuwa Station|ja|北方真桑駅|12=draft|12=draft}}.
=== By Bus === ; {{ill|Gifu Bus|ja|岐阜バス|12=draft|12=draft}} * Alight at "JA Masano Branch" bus stop on the Ōno-Masano-Kitagata Line, an 8-minute walk. ** Departures from {{ill|JR Gifu Station|ja|岐阜駅|12=draft|12=draft}} Bus Terminal (North, Platform 8) or {{ill|Meitetsu Gifu Station|ja|名鉄岐阜駅|12=draft|12=draft}} (West, Platform 6), bound for {{ill|Aeon Town Motosu|ja|イオンタウン本巣|12=draft|12=draft}} or {{ill|Ōno Bus Center|ja|大野バスセンター|12=draft|12=draft}}. ; {{ill|Motosu City Municipal Bus|ja|本巣市市営バス|12=draft|12=draft}} * Alight at "Masano Branch Office" bus stop on the Danjō Line, a 15-minute walk.
== References == {{Reflist}} == See Also == * {{ill|List of Kofun in Japan|en|日本の古墳一覧|12=draft|12=draft}}
